bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,250],"id":"4630d7ee-ff03-167a-c1b3-1258202c42f3","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint A"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint B\n\nGET https://service-b.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,760],"id":"bafbf83e-8e14-d68b-df91-c5018d842b98","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint B"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint C\n\nGET https://service-c.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,1270],"id":"e823e04f-53b8-bc6f-cb9f-53a7591ef9df","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint C"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Combine Probe Results\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: All Healthy?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"d7767ffd-ffbf-f61e-0874-f4ce42411d21","name":"Note: Combine Probe Results"},{"parameters":{"content":"### All Healthy?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ ($json.statusCode || 200) < 400 }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Uptime Metric · ②→ Already Alerted? (State Check)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,520],"id":"240005d0-53eb-d5f5-bed4-f7225c65f65d","name":"Note: All Healthy?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Uptime Metric\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Save Execution Metadata · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,280],"id":"327acfca-ba66-3c10-a16e-c7dcf6915423","name":"Note: Record Uptime Metric"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Already Alerted? (State Check)\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Page On-Call via Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,880],"id":"d0e65fd9-be8f-cdd0-a5a7-44aba4681d49","name":"Note: Already Alerted? (State Check)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Page On-Call via Slack\n\ntwilio — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Twilio SID + token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,880],"id":"3e89a1aa-12e5-0e5a-11d4-e0012d8959e9","name":"Note: Page On-Call via Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Sort Metrics Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"dd13bb80-82e5-b34d-90f4-0f381c22d57f","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Metrics Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Send Summary to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"301c6290-e96b-1104-3724-28a442a7957e","name":"Note: Sort Metrics Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"a20db090-ddb8-6d45-6a37-f5ab82195dee","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,1540],"id":"aa12b813-30ac-3a89-88c9-4017175c80b5","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,1540],"id":"d7e46d7f-57ea-09a0-2838-fab697298428","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Alert on stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Twilio hands-free\n\n**Pattern:** Threshold Monitoring · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAlert on stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Twilio hands-free. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual alerts is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Probe Endpoint A → Combine Probe Results → All Healthy? → Record Uptime Metric → Save Execution Metadata → Sort Metrics Newest First → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to threshold monitoring without manual effort\n- Anyone automating alerts in data\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2; Twilio SID + token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"2efad6ed-816a-ffc6-f04a-3f282d433ea6","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"e2596fad-6c0b-ea8f-dfd6-7c5e38a877df","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"43b2180a-1a86-4e5b-b179-6fafd7e5abb3","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your alerts process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"dd7657a0-2375-8119-a6f6-00b432e9feee","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Every Few Minutes":{"main":[[{"node":"Probe Endpoint A","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint B","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint C","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint A":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint B":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":1}]]},"Probe Endpoint C":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":2}]]},"Combine Probe Results":{"main":[[{"node":"All Healthy?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"All Healthy?":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Uptime Metric","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Already Alerted? (State Check)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Already Alerted? (State Check)":{"main":[[{"node":"Page On-Call via Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Uptime Metric":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Metrics Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Metrics Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Page On-Call via Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"50a02e87-18c0-45bd-be1e-e3284ec8101c","id":"FDX10236"}